{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":26504,"name":"Victor","username":"k7x","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/k7x/{size}/3780_2.png","created_at":"2018-11-05T15:29:30.326Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello\u003cbr\u003e\nI have a problem. I am writing a program for artists. The platform is an android. One of the important components of this program is to save the render to a file. That is a picture.\u003cbr\u003e\nThe function to make a screenshot is not suitable. I need a specific size of the picture.\u003cbr\u003e\nI tried to make an ordinary render to the texture, get a picture from the texture and save it to PNG. Used RGBA\u003cbr\u003e\nBut in the place of the picture I was getting a noise or something like that.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHelp please solve this problem.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-11-09T17:56:48.317Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":105,"reads":44,"readers_count":43,"score":533.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":4646,"topic_slug":"render-to-texture-save-as-png","display_username":"Victor","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1048,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":26506,"name":"Jonathan","username":"Sinoid","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2018-11-05T17:36:50.136Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003ePost your code. There’s too many ways you could be trying to do this.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou should just be using \u003ccode\u003eGetImage()\u003c/code\u003e and \u003ccode\u003eImage::SavePNG\u003c/code\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-11-05T17:36:50.136Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":45,"readers_count":44,"score":34.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":4646,"topic_slug":"render-to-texture-save-as-png","display_username":"Jonathan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":669,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":26507,"name":"Victor","username":"k7x","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/k7x/{size}/3780_2.png","created_at":"2018-11-05T18:09:08.264Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI am using some like this :\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003eNode@ renderCameraNode = scene0.CreateChild(\"RenderCamera\");\nCamera@ renderCamera = renderCameraNode.CreateComponent(\"Camera\");\nrenderCamera.orthographics = true;\n\nTexture2D@ renderTexture = Texture2D();\nrenderTexture.SetSize(512, 512, GetRGBAFormat(), TEXTURE_RENDERTARGET);\nMaterial@ renderMaterial = Material();\nrenderMaterial.SetTechnique(0, cache.GetResource(\"Technique\", \"Techniques/DiffUnlit.xml\"));\nrenderMaterial.SetTexture(TU_DIFFUSE, renderTexture);\n\nRenderSurface@ surface = renderTexture.GetRenderSurface();\nViewport@ rttViewport = Viewport(scene0, renderCamera);\nsurface.SetViewport(0, rttViewport); \n\nTexture2D@ texture = surface.parentTexture;\nImage@ image = texture.GetImage();\n\nimage.SavePNG(\"data/render.png\");\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethis code is running at the end of start() function\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI try do engine.RunFrame() before save\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-11-05T19:49:30.069Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":43,"readers_count":42,"score":33.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":4646,"topic_slug":"render-to-texture-save-as-png","display_username":"Victor","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1048,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":26509,"name":"Jonathan","username":"Sinoid","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/f19dbf/{size}.png","created_at":"2018-11-05T18:52:57.289Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eProbably need to set the surface update mode to always, the stuff with the image looks fine.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBy default surfaces only render when visible. You’re probably getting whatever gobbly-gook your driver gives an uninitialized texture (noise, it’s usually a pattern though).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSurfaces do send an event, so you can subscribe to that to save the image when you know it’s really there.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-11-05T18:52:57.289Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":28.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":4646,"topic_slug":"render-to-texture-save-as-png","display_username":"Jonathan","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":669,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":26510,"name":"Victor","username":"k7x","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/k7x/{size}/3780_2.png","created_at":"2018-11-05T18:56:24.198Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI also tried to render the entire scene with the plane on which the rendering will take place, but all the same could not save the result in png\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI try always update\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-11-05T18:57:36.340Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":8.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":4646,"topic_slug":"render-to-texture-save-as-png","display_username":"Victor","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1048,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":26522,"name":"Victor","username":"k7x","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/k7x/{size}/3780_2.png","created_at":"2018-11-06T10:57:25.018Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI try do update always but output still noise\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-11-06T10:57:25.018Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":38,"readers_count":37,"score":12.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":4646,"topic_slug":"render-to-texture-save-as-png","display_username":"Victor","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":1048,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":26572,"name":"Victor","username":"k7x","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/k7x/{size}/3780_2.png","created_at":"2018-11-09T10:02:53.758Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eFinally it happened!\u003cbr\u003e\nAll you need to do is\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003euse lines of code not in the Start () function but after\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUse RGBA texture format\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSurface.update = update always\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBefore getting the image from the texture, exec engine.RunFrame()\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAfter get the image save\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI think my mistake was that I used lines of the render code to the texture in the start function. Perhaps this is a specific device error.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThank for the help!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2018-11-09T17:56:56.956Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":31,"readers_count":30,"score":6.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":4646,"topic_slug":"render-to-texture-save-as-png","display_username":"Victor","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":nu